Children's Hospital named sixth-best

SECTION: ASECTION; Pg. 2A

LENGTH: 94 words


Children's Hospital of Colorado in Aurora has been ranked sixth in the U.S. News
& World Report's Best Children's Hospitals honor roll for 2014 15.

The rankings, which were based on survival rates, adequacy of nursing staff and
procedure volume, analyzed the performance of hundreds of hospitals nationwide
in 10 specialties. Of the 89 hospitals ranked in the specialties, just 10 were
chosen for the honor roll.

The rankings are aimed to best guide families of children with life threatening
or rare conditions to the best medical care available, the publisher said.

